FBIS3-29586 "dreas035_g_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 SOUTHEAST ASIA Burma Trawlers Warned To Avoid Oil Exploration Site BK1802150794 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 18 Feb 94 BK1802150794 Rangoon Radio Burma Language: Burmese Article Type:BFN [Text] According to the agreement reached between the Myanmar [Burma] Oil and Gas Enterprise and Texaco Exploration Myanmar and Corporation, drilling operations at Ye Mahn Aung-1 -- a test well in oil exploration block M-13 offshore from Tenasserim -- will begin on 14 February. It is estimated that drilling operations will last for about 45 days. A mariners' notice has been issued warning fishing trawlers to refrain from entering the vicinity of Ye Mahn Aung-1: North latitude 13 degrees, 17 minutes, and 41.70 seconds; and East longitude 96 degrees, 58 minutes, and 31.40 seconds.
